#X text 625 284 complex;
#X text 52 381 If (b^2 - 4.c) is negative \, we're extracting a square root of a negative value \, hence we're dealing with a complex number! That means: a Complex Pole! So we need to check if it's positive or negative. If positive \, this is the real part and the imaginary part is 0 \, but if negative \, it's the imaginary part and the real part is 0 - we then have both parts as:;
